==English==
{{wikipedia}}
===Etymology===
Italian [[tarantella#Italian|tarantella]], a diminutive of [[w:Taranto|Taranto]], a town in southern Italy (but popularly associated with [[tarantola]] ‘tarantula’).

===Pronunciation===
*(US) {{IPA|/ˌtɛrənˈtɛlə/}}
*(RP) {{IPA|/tærən'tɛlə/}}
*{{audio|en-us-tarantella.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}
# a rapid [[dance]] in 6/8 time, originating in Italy, or a piece of music for such a dance

